    "department": "Product Management",
    "description": "Duties\n\n - Create product vision and strategy, including by defining long-term direction, setting measurable success metrics, and identifying market opportunities.\n\n - Create product roadmap, including by building and maintaining release plans, prioritizing features based on impact and resources, and communicating the roadmap to stakeholders.\n\n - Stakeholder alignment and communication, including by building consensus with leadership and cross-functional teams and resolving competing priorities.\n\n - Guide analytics and market research, including by directing analysis to support decision-making and validating market sizing.\n\n - Conduct high-level UX research oversight, including by approving scope and methods and ensuring insights inform roadmap.\n\n - Approve product designs, including by reviewing final UX/UI and validating alignment with strategy and user needs.\n\nRequirements\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in Engineering (any), Computer Science, or related field, or foreign equivalent\n\n - Two (2) years of experience in the job offered or a related occupation performing product management services within the cryptocurrency or financial technology space.\n\n - Experience must include utilizing Figma design tools; leveraging project management software such as Jira or Linear; working with fintech products; working on Bitcoin wallets; building on Bitcoin Layer 2 technologies; working on brokerage trading tools and experiences; cross-functional communication and collaboration; conducting UX research; working with compliance teams; creating marketing assets; working with operational teams; UX design; product and feature design; and performing data analysis and analytics.\n\nLocation and Salary\n\n - Teleworking allowed within commutable distance of River Financial, Inc.’s offices in San Francisco, CA, New York, NY, and Columbus, OH.\n\n - Salary range between $87,464 to $220,000 per year\n\n - Significant equity stock options\n\n - Medical, Dental and Vision Benefits\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - Parental Leave separate from regular PTO policy\n\n - 401k",
